      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING KLIMENKO (1) turned in a moderate performance last time when seventh at Gosford over 388m behind Ibrox Maverick (23.02) in a Grade 5. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Better than last start and worth following up. MIDNIGHT MOHAWK (3) has mixed form recently, finishing sixth (22.87) in a Grade 5 at Gosford latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Good beginner and aided by a handy draw. Well placed here and should do much better. TARA REBEL (8) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Finished third (22.72) at Gosford last time making it three minors on end. Has a good record here including two wins. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Bold showing expected. ZIPPING TANAKA (2) can run a bold race on best form.",
